b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Height is best suited for product teams, cross functional teams, modern teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Monday.com AI, meanwhile, shines for marketing teams, operations, mid size companies, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Height describes itself as \"AI-native project management tool that automates task organization and updates.\" Monday.com AI, established in 2012, positions itself as \"Work OS with AI-powered automation, project tracking, and team collaboration.\" With 7 years between them, Monday.com AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Height offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Monday.com AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Height is a poor choice — far from it. Height excels in its own right, particularly for product teams and cross functional teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value beautiful and intuitive board interface, go with Monday.com AI. If ai automatically categorizes and updates tasks matters more to you, Height is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
